.TH "nfp_cpp_area_alloc_acquire" 9 "nfp_cpp_area_alloc_acquire" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfp_cpp_area_alloc_acquire \- allocate a new CPP area and lock it down
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct nfp_cpp_area *" nfp_cpp_area_alloc_acquire
.BI "(struct nfp_cpp *cpp "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "u32 dest "  ","
.BI "unsigned long long address "  ","
.BI "unsigned long size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpp" 12
CPP handle
.IP "name" 12
Name of region
.IP "dest" 12
CPP id
.IP "address" 12
Start address on CPP target
.IP "size" 12
Size of area
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate and initialize a CPP area structure, and lock it down so
that it can be accessed directly.
.SH "NOTE"
\fIaddress\fP and \fIsize\fP must be 32-bit aligned values.
The area must also be 'released' when the structure is freed.
.SH "RETURN"
NFP CPP Area handle, or NULL
